isible Woman]]'').<ref>{{cite news|url=https://scifibulletin.com/2020/03/23/rip-david-collings/|title=RIP David Collings|publisher=SciFi Bulletin|date=24 March 2020}}</ref>\n**[[Tristan Garel-Jones]], 79, politician, [[Member of Parliament|MP]] (1979\u20131997), [[Minister for Europe]] (1990\u20131993) and [[Treasurer of the Household]] (1989\u20131990).<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/obituaries/2020/03/24/tristan-garel-jonestory-wet-able-deputy-chief-whip-margaret/|title=Tristan Garel-Jones, Tory 'wet' and able deputy chief whip under Margaret Thatcher \u2013 obituary|work=The Telegraph|date=24 March 2020|access-date=27 March 2020}} {{registration}}</ref>\n**[[William Stern (businessman)|William Stern]], 84, Hungarian-born businessman, first notable British victim of [[Coronavirus disease 2019|COVID-19]].<ref>{{cite news|last=Weaver|first=Matthew|url=https://www.theguardian.com/world/2020/mar/23/devastating-vicar-and-headteacher-among-latest-named-uk-coronavirus-victims|title='Devastating': vicar and headteacher among latest UK coronavirus victims|work=The Guardian|date=23 March 2020|access-date=27 March 2020}}</ref> (death announced on this date)\n*24 March\n**[[John Campbell-Jones]], 90, [[Formula One]] driver.<ref>{{cite web|title=John Campbell-Jones|url=https://www.oldracingcars.com/driver/John_Campbell-Jones|website=Old Racing Cars|accessdate=27 March 2020}}</ref>\n**[[Steven Dick]], 37, diplomat, Deputy British Ambassador to Hungary (since 2019), [[Coronavirus disease 2019|COVID-19]].<ref>{{cite news|title=Coronavirus: Scottish diplomat Steven Dick dies in Hungary|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-scotland-52042786|work=BBC News|publisher=BBC|date=25 March 2020}}</ref>\n**[[Tony Rutter]], 78, motorcycle racer, [[Formula TT]] world champion (1981\u20131984).<ref>{{cite web|last1=White|first1=Kyle|title=Racing legend Tony Rutter sadly passes away|url=https://www.newsletter.co.uk/sport/motorcycling/racing-legend-tony-rutter-sadly-passes-away-251