m in the United Kingdom|terrorist]]-related.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-england-london-51349664 |title=Streatham attack: Man shot dead by police after stabbings in London |work=BBC News |publisher=BBC |date=2 February 2020 |accessdate=2 February 2020}}</ref>\n*4 February \u2013 In London, Prime Minister Boris Johnson, naturalist [[David Attenborough|Sir David Attenborough]], and Italian Prime Minister [[Giuseppe Conte]] launch the [[COP26|26th session of the Conference of the Parties]] (COP26), a major UN climate summit to be held in Glasgow in November 2020.<ref name=BBC_51366123/> Johnson announces, subject to consultation, that coal power could be phased out by 2024, a year earlier than previously planned and the phase-out of new petrol and diesel vehicles could be brought forward from 2040 to 2035.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/politics/2020/02/04/coal-power-phased-2024-boris-johnson-says-uk-has-duty-fight/|title=Coal power to be phased out by 2024 as Boris Johnson says UK has duty to fight climate change as first industrialised nation|newspaper=Telegraph|language=en|date=2020-02-04|access-date=2020-02-05|last1=Yorke|first1=Harry}}</ref><ref name=BBC_51366123>{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/science-environment-51366123|title=Petrol and diesel car sales ban brought forward to 2035|website=BBC News|language=en|date=2020-02-04|access-date=2020-02-05}}</ref> He also reaffirms the UK's commitment to reaching net zero carbon by 2050.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.gov.uk/government/news/pm-launches-un-climate-summit-in-the-uk|title=PM launches UN Climate Summit in the UK|website=GOV.UK|language=en|access-date=2020-02-05}}</ref>\n*6 February \u2013 [[COVID-19 in the UK]]: A third case of coronavirus is confirmed in the UK.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-51398039|title=Coronavirus: Third case confirmed in the UK\n|website=BBC News|language=en|date=2020-02-06|access-date=2020-02-06}}</ref>\n*7 February \u2013 [[Buckingham Palace]] announces that the wedding of [[Princess Beatrice of York]] and [[Edoardo Mapelli Mozzi]] will take place on 29 May.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-51415860 |title=Princess Beatrice: Royal wedding to be held on 29 May |work=BBC News |publisher=BBC |date=7 February 2020 |accessdate=7 February 2020}}</ref>\n*8\u20139 February \u2013 [[Storm Ciara]] hits the United Kingdom, bringing winds of up to {{convert|80|mph|abbr=on}}.\n*9 February \u2013 A British Airways [[Boeing 747]] aircraft makes the fastest ever subsonic New York JFK to London Heathrow crossing, achieved in 4 hours 56 minutes. It reaches ground speeds of up to 825&nbsp;mph by riding the jet stream bringing [[Storm Ciara]] to the UK.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.bbc.com/news/uk-england-london-51433720|title=Storm helps plane beat transatlantic flight record|work=BBC News|date=9 February 2020}}</ref>\n*10 February\n**The government confirms it has begun to study the feasibility of a [[Irish Sea Bridge|Scotland-Northern Ireland bridge]], with project cost estimates of \u00a315\u201320bn.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.theguardian.com/politics/2020/feb/10/boris-johnson-northern-ireland-scotland-bridge-plan-being-actively-looked-into-no-10|title=Government 'actively looking into' Scotland-Northern Ireland bridge|website=The Guardian|language=en|date=2020-02-10|access-date=2020-02-11}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-politics-51443191|title=Work 'under way' into Scotland-Northern Ireland bridge feasibility|website=BBC News|language=en|date=2020-02-10|access-date=2020-02-11}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.heraldscotland.com/news/18224365.whitehall-officials-begin-scoping-work-boris-bridge-linking-scotland-n-ireland/|title=Whitehall officials begin 'scoping work' on Boris Bridge linking Scotland and Northern Ireland|website=The Herald|language=en|date=2020-02-10|access-date=2020-02-11}}</ref>\n**In a \"historic\" decision, councillors